### 🖥️ Project Showcase: Claude UI Strategy Dashboard
The full visual codebase has been built and rendered into an accessible frontend template. The asset layers break down into two core structural protocols:

#### 1. Model Selection Matrix
* **⚡ Haiku 4.5 `[Low Effort]`** ➔ **Speed Optimization:** Deployed strictly for quick syntax checks (e.g., Spring Boot annotation lookups) and fast, flashcard-style Q&A review loops.
* **⚖️ Sonnet 4.6 `[Medium / Standard Effort]`** ➔ **The Daily Workhorse:** Your primary execution environment. Configured for writing CRUD API components, handling multi-layer debugging, and parsing complex Java design patterns.
* **🏆 Opus 4.8 `[High / Max Effort]`** ➔ **Heavy-Duty Architecture:** Reserved for high-stakes foundational tasks. Deployed during initial system architecture design or when managing advanced agentic AI orchestration nodes.

#### 2. Daily Task Routing Protocol
The deployed system utilizes the following algorithmic task distribution map:

| Task Category | Target Model | Required Effort Level | Strategic Justification |
| :--- | :---: | :---: | :--- |
| **Syntax / Concept Lookups** | Haiku 4.5 | Low 🔋 | Preserves primary workspace token limits. |
| **CRUD API Development** | Sonnet 4.6 | Medium (Standard) 🪫 | Optimal balance between context reasoning and token cost. |
| **Tricky Spring Boot Debugging** | Sonnet 4.6 | High 🔋 | Traces layered errors (Controller ➔ Service ➔ Repo). |
| **Flagship Public Content Polish** | Sonnet/Opus | High 🔋 | Maximizes linguistic tone and engagement metrics. |
| **Initial API System Architecture** | Opus 4.8 | Max 🔌 | High-impact structural setup that is expensive to refactor later. |

---

### ⚠️ Critical System Guardrails (Antipatterns Avoided)
* **01 / Allocating Max/Opus to Vague Inquiries:** Avoids burning daily inference quotas on simple logic tasks where smaller models yield identical alpha.
* **02 / Under-prompting Advanced Concept Tracks:** Enforces a ban on using low-effort or lightweight configurations for steep learning curves, neutralizing the risk of superficial comprehension.
* **03 / Static Context Settings:** Enforces dynamic, real-time mid-conversation shifts in model tiers as task complexity changes within a single chat workspace.

